    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 4,5: subcellular fractions from rat striatum showed that PDE10A is localized to postsynaptic fractions, associates with membrane fractions but not the PSD fraction (like e.g. NMDA1 and PSD95). Authors conclude; \"These results suggest that PDE10A associates with membranes through a non-ionic interaction.\"\n\nFigure 7: Localization of PDE10A in rat striatum by immuno-electron microscopy. Particles were observed at the edge of PSDs but not directly apposed to these structures (and not in presynaptic terminals at all).. Experimental description: Figure 7: \"Localization of PDE10A in rat striatum\"\n\nantibody:\nPDE10A mouse monoclonal antibody 24F3.F11 (1:1000)",
